Then $OM = 16$ inches, so $EM = 8$ inches.  Also, $EF = FG = GH = HE = 16$ inches.

Let $x$ be the side length of the square base of the frustum.  Then by similar triangles, $\frac{8}{x} = \frac{1}{4},$ so $x = 32.$  Then the side length of the top face of the frustum is 16 inches.

Let $O'$ be the apex of the frustum.  Then $OO'$ is the altitude of the frustum, and $OO' = \frac{1}{4} OP = 3$ inches.  Also, $O'M = OM - OO' = 13$ inches.

