The volume of the original pyramid is $\frac{1}{3} \cdot 32^2 \cdot 12 = 4096$ cubic inches, and the volume of the frustum is
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{3} \cdot 16^2 \cdot 3 + \frac{1}{3} \cdot 32^2 \cdot 9 - \frac{1}{3} \cdot 16^2 \cdot 9 &= 144 + 768 - 192 \\
&= 720.
\end{align*}Therefore, the volume of the remaining frustum is $\frac{720}{4096} = \boxed{\frac{45}{256}}$ of the volume of the original pyramid.

